TASK 1 :- Code Standard For Java

1. Use snake casing to name the packages.
2. Use pascal casing to name the classes and interfaces.
3. Use the camel casing to name the methods and variables.
4. Use the proper variable name, class & interface name, method name.
5. Make use of proper indentation and spacing when required.
6. Use proper comment for good code understanding and readability.


for example:

public class PersonInfo
{
	public static void main(String [] args)
	{
		String name = "Shivam Thakur";
		int age = 22;
		String jobRole = "Trainee";
		
		System.out.println("Name :" +name);
		System.out.println("Age :" +age);
		System.out.println("Job Role :" +jobRole);
	}
}

TASK 2 :- Sonar Lint

It is a extension used for check the spell mistakes in the code, proper use of naming format and to check the quality of the code. 
Sonar Lint help us to fix the mistakes in the code before saving and committing.

